answers.body_markdown:
The `beforeCreate` hook runs at the initialization of your component: **data has not been made reactive**, and events have not been set up yet. Have a look at https://vuejs.org/v2/api/#beforeCreate and https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/instance.html#Lifecycle-Diagram.

It is quite &quot;standard&quot; to use the `created` hook for fetching a Firestore database (or any other API). In this hook, you will be able to access reactive data.

So just modify

      async beforeCreate () {
         //.....
      }

to

      async created () {
         //.....
      }

